            "text": {
              "status": "generated",
              "div": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"><h3>Annotation</h3><table class=\"hl7__eu__lab__report\"><tr><th>Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us</th></tr><tr><td>The laboratory results show a mildly elevated HbA1c (5.9%), indicating prediabetes, while fasting glucose is within normal limits. Renal function (urea, creatinine), electrolytes, and calcium are all within normal ranges. Total CO₂ is slightly low, which may suggest mild metabolic acidosis or compensated respiratory alkalosis; clinical correlation is advised. No other significant abnormalities detected.</td></tr></table></div>"
